text: Grosvenor House may refer to: *Grosvenor House, a former building in Park Lane, London, UK *Grosvenor House Hotel, a hotel in Mayfair, London, UK *Grosvenor House (Dubai), a hotel in Dubai, UAE *E.O. Grosvenor House, a house museum in Jonesville, Michigan, USA * Grosvenor House, a de Havilland DH.88 Comet aircraft which won the MacRobertson Air Race from the UK to Australia in 1934; the aircraft's owner was the manager of the Grosvenor House Hotel
title: Grosvenor House (disambiguation)
